3AW host John Burns has been accused of calling Bachar Houli a 'terrorist' at a club function at the MCG on Friday night . 
  Mr Burns said he doesn't recall making the comment and is 'mortified' by the allegation . 
  He apologised 'unreservedly' to the people at the event and the Richmond Football Club . 
  The radio station confirmed a complaint has been made against Mr Burns . 
  He is alleged to have referred to Houlo as a ' terrorist' at the club function . 
  The comment was allegedly made during the Tigers' match against Melbourne . 
  He said a friend sitting with him at the time also didn't recall the comment being made . 
 